@startuml C4 Code Level - ML Drift Detection Pipeline
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam classBackgroundColor #F0F0F0
skinparam arrowColor #333333
skinparam classBorderColor #333333

title C4 Code Level: ML Drift Detection Pipeline\n(airflow_pipeline/dags/drift_detection_pipeline.py)

package "drift_detection_pipeline.py" {

    package "Configuration & Constants" {
        class DriftConfig {
            + CLASS_NAMES: [str] × 6 (beauty_salon, drugstore, restaurant, movie_theater, apartment_building, supermarket)
            + DRIFT_THRESHOLD: float = 0.25
            + WINDOW_DAYS: int = 7
            + MIN_ROWS_FOR_DRIFT: int = 20
            + REJECTION_RATE_THRESHOLD: float = 0.30
            + MIN_REVIEWED_IN_WINDOW: int = 10
            + RETRAIN_COOLDOWN_DAYS: int = 7
            + DRIFT_PERSISTENCE_WINDOW: int = 5
            + DRIFT_PERSISTENCE_K: int = 3
        }

        class DriftPaths {
            + DRIFT_DIR: Path = /opt/airflow/data/drift
            + BASELINE_JSON: Path = DRIFT_DIR / baseline_reference.json
            + REPORTS_DIR: Path = DRIFT_DIR / reports
        }

        class DatabaseUrl {
            + PREDICTIONS_DATABASE_URL: str = postgresql://predictions:predictions@predictions-db:5432/predictions
        }
    }

    package "Baseline Management (Task 1)" {
        class bootstrap_baseline_task {
            + bootstrap_baseline_task(**context): Dict[str, Any]
            --
            - check if baseline_reference.json exists
            - if not exists:
              * if df is empty: return uniform distribution
              * else: bootstrap from earliest 500 prediction_logs rows
            - write class_distribution + quality_reference (brightness, blur_score)
            - returns {status: 'created'|'exists', path: str}
        }

        class _ensure_dirs {
            + {static} _ensure_dirs()
            --
            - mkdir DRIFT_DIR, REPORTS_DIR
        }
    }

    package "Data Read/Prepare" {
        class _read_logs {
            + {static} _read_logs(): pd.DataFrame
            --
            - SQL: SELECT from prediction_logs ORDER BY timestamp ASC
            - parse timestamp (UTC), dropna (timestamp, predicted_class, brightness, blur_score)
        }

        class _uniform_class_distribution {
            + {static} _uniform_class_distribution(): Dict[str, float]
            --
            - return {class: 1/6 for all 6 classes}
        }

        class _normalize_distribution {
            + {static} _normalize_distribution(counts: Dict, categories: List): Dict[str, float]
            --
            - normalize class counts to probabilities
            - fallback to uniform if total ≤ 0
        }
    }

    package "Stability Index (PSI/CSI) Computation" {
        class _stability_index {
            + {static} _stability_index(expected: ndarray, actual: ndarray, eps: float = 1e-6): float
            --
            - compute sum((actual - expected) * log(actual / expected))
            - clip values to [eps, ∞) to avoid log(0)
        }

        class _psi_from_class_distributions {
            + {static} _psi_from_class_distributions(expected_dist: Dict, actual_dist: Dict): float
            --
            - extract probabilities from both dicts in CLASS_NAMES order
            - call _stability_index(expected, actual)
        }

        class _compute_bin_edges {
            + {static} _compute_bin_edges(reference_values: ndarray, n_bins: int = 10): ndarray
            --
            - compute percentile quantiles [0, 100] in n_bins+1 steps
            - return unique edges with padding [v-1e-6, v+1e-6]
        }

        class _distribution_from_edges {
            + {static} _distribution_from_edges(values: ndarray, edges: ndarray): ndarray
            --
            - histogram(values, bins=edges)
            - normalize to probabilities
            - fallback to uniform if total ≤ 0
        }

        class _csi_from_samples {
            + {static} _csi_from_samples(expected_values: List[float], actual_values: List[float]): float
            --
            - compute bin edges from expected_values
            - compute distributions for both expected and actual
            - call _stability_index on distributions
            - used for brightness and blur_score
        }
    }

    package "Rejection Rate Computation" {
        class _compute_rejection_rate {
            + {static} _compute_rejection_rate(window_start: datetime, window_end: datetime): (float, int)
            --
            - SQL COUNT FILTER: reviewed = COUNT(*) WHERE review_status IN ('approved', 'rejected')
            - SQL COUNT FILTER: rejected = COUNT(*) WHERE review_status = 'rejected'
            - return (rejected / reviewed, reviewed_count)
            - gate: if reviewed == 0, return (0.0, 0)
        }
    }

    package "Drift Report Generation (Task 2)" {
        class compute_drift_task {
            + compute_drift_task(**context): Dict[str, Any]
            --
            - load baseline_reference.json
            - read_logs() → df
            - compute window [now - WINDOW_DAYS, now)
            - check MIN_ROWS_FOR_DRIFT gate
            - compute 4 signals:
              * PSI over predicted-class distribution
              * CSI over brightness
              * CSI over blur_score
              * rejection_rate (if reviewed_in_window ≥ MIN_REVIEWED_IN_WINDOW)
            - drift_detected = any signal > DRIFT_THRESHOLD
            - save report to latest_report.json and timestamped file
        }

        class DriftReport {
            + generated_at: str (ISO)
            + window_start: str (ISO)
            + window_end: str (ISO)
            + status: str (ok | empty_prediction_logs | insufficient_recent_rows)
            + threshold: float
            + recent_rows: int
            + baseline_mode: str
            + psi: float
            + csi_brightness: float
            + csi_blur_score: float
            + rejection_rate: float (0.0 if no reviews)
            + reviewed_in_window: int
            + drift_detected: bool
            + reasons: List[str] (subset of {psi, csi_brightness, csi_blur_score, rejection_rate})
            + current_class_distribution: Dict[str, float]
            + expected_class_distribution: Dict[str, float]
        }
    }

    package "Retrain Decision (Task 3 - Branching)" {
        class branch_on_drift {
            + branch_on_drift(**context): str
            --
            - pull compute_drift_report xcom → report
            - if NOT report.drift_detected:
              * return "skip_model_retraining"
            - check PERSISTENCE gate:
              * read last DRIFT_PERSISTENCE_WINDOW timestamped reports
              * count how many have drift_detected = True
              * if persisted_count < DRIFT_PERSISTENCE_K: return "skip_model_retraining"
            - check COOLDOWN gate:
              * query Airflow DagRun.find(dag_id="model_training_pipeline")
              * if any run start_date ≥ (now - RETRAIN_COOLDOWN_DAYS): return "skip_model_retraining"
            - else: return "trigger_model_retraining"
        }

        class PersistenceGate {
            + reads: last DRIFT_PERSISTENCE_WINDOW timestamped reports
            + threshold: DRIFT_PERSISTENCE_K of last DRIFT_PERSISTENCE_WINDOW
            + default: 3 of last 5 must have drift_detected=True
        }

        class CooldownGate {
            + checks: Airflow DagRun metadata for model_training_pipeline
            + threshold: RETRAIN_COOLDOWN_DAYS (default 7 days)
            + prevents: rapid cascades of retrains
        }
    }

    package "DAG Orchestration" {
        class DAG_drift_detection_pipeline {
            + dag_id: drift_detection_pipeline
            + schedule: @daily
            + description: Detect production data drift using PSI/CSI
            + catchup: False
            --
            + bootstrap_baseline: PythonOperator(bootstrap_baseline_task)
            + compute_drift_report: PythonOperator(compute_drift_task)
            + decide_retraining: BranchPythonOperator(branch_on_drift)
            + trigger_model_retraining: TriggerDagRunOperator → model_training_pipeline
            + skip_model_retraining: EmptyOperator
            + done: EmptyOperator(trigger_rule=none_failed_min_one_success)
            --
            + flow: bootstrap_baseline >> compute_drift_report >> decide_retraining
            +       decide_retraining >> {trigger_model_retraining | skip_model_retraining} >> done
        }
    }

    package "Dependencies" {
        class PREDICTIONS_DATABASE {
            + url: postgresql://predictions:predictions@predictions-db:5432/predictions
            + schema: prediction_logs (prediction_logs, review_status, final_class, brightness, blur_score)
        }

        class DRIFT_STORAGE {
            + file system: /opt/airflow/data/drift (Docker bind-mount)
            + baseline_reference.json: reference class distribution and quality metrics
            + reports/: timestamped drift_report_*.json + latest_report.json
        }

        class AIRFLOW_METADATA {
            + DagRun.find(): query training DAG run history for cooldown
        }
    }
}

' Relationships
bootstrap_baseline_task --> _ensure_dirs: uses
bootstrap_baseline_task --> _read_logs: uses
bootstrap_baseline_task --> _normalize_distribution: uses
bootstrap_baseline_task --> DRIFT_STORAGE: writes baseline_reference.json

compute_drift_task --> _read_logs: uses
compute_drift_task --> _normalize_distribution: uses
compute_drift_task --> _psi_from_class_distributions: computes
compute_drift_task --> _csi_from_samples: computes (brightness, blur_score)
compute_drift_task --> _compute_rejection_rate: computes
compute_drift_task --> DRIFT_STORAGE: writes latest_report.json and timestamped report

_psi_from_class_distributions --> _stability_index: uses
_csi_from_samples --> _compute_bin_edges: uses
_csi_from_samples --> _distribution_from_edges: uses
_csi_from_samples --> _stability_index: uses

_compute_rejection_rate --> PREDICTIONS_DATABASE: query review_status counts

branch_on_drift --> PersistenceGate: enforces
branch_on_drift --> CooldownGate: enforces
branch_on_drift --> DRIFT_STORAGE: reads timestamped reports
branch_on_drift --> AIRFLOW_METADATA: queries DagRun history

DAG_drift_detection_pipeline --> bootstrap_baseline_task: orchestrates
DAG_drift_detection_pipeline --> compute_drift_task: orchestrates
DAG_drift_detection_pipeline --> branch_on_drift: orchestrates
DAG_drift_detection_pipeline --> TriggerDagRunOperator: conditional trigger to model_training_pipeline

note right of branch_on_drift
    Gating Strategy (applied sequentially):
    1. Drift Detection: only proceed if drift_detected = true
    2. Persistence: K of M recent reports must show drift
    3. Cooldown: model_training_pipeline must not have run recently

    All gates must pass to trigger retrain.
end note

note bottom of DriftReport
    Key signals:
    - PSI: monitors predicted-class distribution shift
    - CSI (brightness): monitors image lighting conditions
    - CSI (blur_score): monitors image sharpness
    - rejection_rate: % of reviewed predictions flagged as incorrect

    drift_detected = True if ANY signal > DRIFT_THRESHOLD
end note

@enduml
